answer: Actually after looking into it more, files cannot be repopulate back into the form, you have two options. The first would be to avoid requiring a form submit for each file and instead use JavaScript to either allow multiple uploads by creating a new field each time, or you could use JavaScript and Ajax to upload them from the form itself. The other option is to save the files temporarily and create some sort of ID system to identify that those files belong to that users form and remove them after a set time. Personally I would just use JavaScript though to and then just have one submit button.
